	<article id="post-2251" class="post-2251 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-civil-liberties category-current-affairs category-democracy category-it category-law category-politics category-tv tag-censorship tag-iceland tag-internet tag-porn tag-rt tag-tv">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/02/rt-interview-about-censorship-of-internet-porn.html" title="Permalink to RT interview about censorship of internet porn" rel="bookmark"><span class="caps">RT</span> interview about censorship of internet porn</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/02/rt-interview-about-censorship-of-internet-porn.html" title="19:25" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2013-02-22T19:25:06+00:00" pubdate>February 22, 2013</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="byauthor">Annie Machon</span></span></span><br>
                                <a href="#" onclick="javascript:copyToClipboard('http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/02/rt-interview-about-censorship-of-internet-porn.html')">Copy permalink to clipboard</a>
                                <br>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>Coin­cid­ent­ally, while in Ice­land I was invited on to <span class="caps">RT</span> to do an inter­view about the country’s pro­posal to cen­sor the inter­net in order to stop access to viol­ent porn.  I stress that this dis­cus­sion is still, appar­ently, at a con­sultat­ive stage — decisions have yet to be taken.<br />
<iframe src="http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/Yc7yp1quBYw" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>
